::: {.notes}
SPEAKER NOTES — Slide 1: The Problem

Open with the scale.

47.4 million Americans live in food-insecure households today. That includes
1 in 5 American children. This is not a fringe issue — it touches every
state, every congressional district, every school in the country.

The chart on the right shows why: at the state level, poverty and food
insecurity move together. The correlation is r = 0.75. Where poverty is high,
hunger follows.

This is the foundation of the brief. The next slide goes one level deeper
into how poverty drives food insecurity — and then we'll look at who is
most affected.

Pause for ~3 seconds before advancing. Let the scale of the number land.
